    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "#Step 4: Core 4-Step Training Loop"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "TiXOtqbFQ3Pf"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "#Research/Learn:\n",
        "\n",
        " Deep understanding of the four fundamental steps\n",
        "  * Forward pass: the process of passing input data through the network layers to produce predictions/outputs.\n",
        "  \n",
        "  * Loss calculation: quantifying how wrong the model's predictions are compared to the ground truth.\n",
        "  \n",
        "  * Backward pass:  computing gradients of the loss with respect to every parameter using the chain rule.\n",
        "  \n",
        "  * Optimization: using computed gradients to adjust weights in a direction that reduces loss\n",
        "   \n",
        "  How they aplly across model types: In training loop per batch, input datas go into Forward pass( prediction)-> loss calculation(scalar error value)-> backward pass (gradients for all params) -> optimize(updated weight) and repeat for next batch\n",
        "\n",
        "Use of accelerate for scaling: Accelerate is a library by Hugging Face that makes distributed training simple by abstracting away hardware-specific code. With key Features:\n",
        "  * Automatic Device Placement: handles all device placement\n",
        "  * Mixed Precision Training: enable automatic mixed precision (FP16)\n",
        "  * Accumulate gradients over multiple steps\n",
        "  * Saving model\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "0WDvPr5Agp0F"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "# Actions: Implement and compare high-level Trainer versus manual training loop.\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "mXNZR9u0BO3D"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "First: Load dataset with dataset have 4 columns: index, sentence1,senctence2, label. I can train classification model to this classifier dataset."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "CeG4qjcED7KA"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "from datasets import load_dataset\n",
        "checkpoint = \"bert-base-uncased\"\n",
        "raw_datasets= load_dataset(\"glue\", \"mrpc\")\n",
        "\n"
